{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"The plan-review gate's deterministic check **P2 (\"resolution\") abstained `no_repo_root`** on the normal `attested` CLI/library path, so the LLM plan-completeness findings could not be code-grounded and landed as `indeterminate / reason: no-verification` (validity 0, severity none) instead of being verified into advisory or dropped. The verdict still computed (PASS when 0 blocking), but the review was running effectively blind to the code.\n\n## Root cause (proven via joe-debug, runtime evidence)\nThere is no single authoritative resolver for the gate's *code read-root*; it was threaded ad-hoc across five hops (`review_plan → produce_plan_review_verdict → run_workflow → StepContext → workflow op → assemble_context`) and dropped to `None` at the workflow boundary. The det-floor op `plan_review_precheck` called `assemble_context(tid, repo_root=None)` with no `cfg`, so `PlanContext.repo_root` was `None` and `det_floor.p2_resolution` abstained `no_repo_root` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py:227`). The degraded/step-budget-fail path ran the det floor on the *original* ctx (which had `repo_root`), which is why a step-budget-failed run showed P2 **pass** — the inconsistency fingerprint. Runtime evidence: `precheck(repo_root=None)` → abstain `no_repo_root`; `precheck(repo_root=<dir>)` → P2 ran (11 refs, 9 resolved).\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. From the repo venv: `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS=50 rebar review-plan <task-id> -o json`.\n2. Inspect `coverage.det.P2` → before the fix: `{\"status\": \"abstain\", \"ran\": false, \"reason\": \"no_repo_root\"}`.\n3. Observe the LLM findings come back as `indeterminate` with `reason: \"no-verification\"`.\n\n- **Expected:** in a gate run an attested snapshot is active (origin/main HEAD by default), so P2 runs against it (`ran: true`) and findings are code-grounded.\n- **Actual:** P2 abstains `no_repo_root`; findings are parked as `no-verification` indeterminate.\n\n## Fix (class-level, not just the immediate bug)\nCentralize code-read-root resolution into a single resolver and use it at the assembly seam, so the \"None → silent degrade\" class is eliminated and the snapshot defaults to origin/main HEAD cleanly when nothing is specified:\n- `rebar.llm.config.resolve_code_root(repo_root=None, *, cfg_repo_path=None, allow_checkout_fallback=True)` — cascade: explicit `repo_root` > `cfg.repo_path` > active attested snapshot (`current_code_root`, origin/main HEAD by default) > live checkout. Default never returns None; `allow_checkout_fallback=False` yields snapshot-or-None for lightweight builders that must not force a checkout root (which would induce cache writes).\n- `orchestrator.assemble_context` resolves the `PlanContext.repo_root` **field** via the resolver (`allow_checkout_fallback=False` → snapshot-or-None) — so EVERY workflow det-floor/grounding op picks up the active snapshot, while the op's `repo_root` ARG (the ticket-store read-root) is untouched.\n\n### Key invariant: code read-root vs ticket-store read-root are DISTINCT\nThe workflow's `repo_root` is the **ticket-store** read-root (it reaches `assemble_context`'s `rebar.show_ticket(repo_root=…)` via `StepContext`) — NOT the code read-root, which is a separate snapshot (`cfg.repo_path`/`current_code_root`). Threading the *code* snapshot through the workflow `repo_root` breaks ticket reads (\"Ticket not found\"), because the ticket store is not under the .git-less code snapshot. `produce_plan_review_verdict` therefore passes its ticket-store `repo_root` through UNCHANGED (a NOTE documents this); the code root is resolved at the `assemble_context` seam, and the agentic verifier reads code via `cfg.repo_path`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A single `resolve_code_root` resolver exists with the documented cascade; never returns None by default; `allow_checkout_fallback=False` returns snapshot-or-None (unit test `test_resolve_code_root_cascade` covers all four levels + the None branch).\n- [ ] `assemble_context` no longer yields `PlanContext.repo_root=None` when an attested snapshot is active; off-gate callers (no snapshot, no cfg) keep `None` (no checkout-write regression).\n- [ ] The code read-root and the ticket-store read-root are kept distinct: `plan_review_precheck` grounds P2 against the active code snapshot WITHOUT hijacking the ticket-store root, and `produce_plan_review_verdict` passes the ticket-store `repo_root` through unchanged (never substitutes `cfg.repo_path`) — regression tests assert both, with a mutation check.\n- [ ] A real `rebar review-plan` in attested mode reports `coverage.det.P2.ran == true` (not `no_repo_root`) and findings are grounded (the `no-verification` indeterminate set collapses). Verified: verdict PASS, P2 ran (11 refs, 9 resolved), indeterminate findings 6 → 1.\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make typecheck` clean; the plan_review/workflow/config unit suites pass with no repo-root leak-guard failures."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782661003480082001,"uuid":"ef61290c-dd66-44b6-82b4-986838eaf6af"}